# Enterprise Non-Negotiables

These instructions are mandatory for all substantial tasks in this project.

- Do not deliver patchwork or temporary fixes.
- Prefer durable, production-grade architecture and operational safety.
- Every significant technical decision must be research-backed using current docs/findings.
- Verify external APIs/libraries against latest references before coding.
- If latest findings cannot be verified, stop and explicitly report the verification gap.

## Planning First (Required)

- Always produce a clear plan before implementation work.
- Do not start coding until the user approves the plan.
- For ambiguous requirements, ask clarifying questions before implementation.

## Implementation Quality Bar

- Align with existing `.cursor/rules` standards (backend, testing, architecture, deployment).
- Include migration-safe updates across all dependent files (no orphan imports/usages).
- Add or update tests for changed behavior and run project-standard test commands.
- Report what was verified (research + tests) and what remains unverified.
